The article is a transcript of remarks made by DJ Gribbin at the AASHTO Washington Briefing on March 1, 2018. Gribbin discusses the Administration's plan for infrastructure and acknowledges the importance of AASHTO in the conversation. He emphasizes the need for a solution that provides safe and reliable infrastructure for the American people. Gribbin also addresses the issue of the Highway Trust Fund and highlights the additional priorities of the plan. He dispels myths about the plan, particularly regarding the permitting process. Gribbin concludes by expressing gratitude for the work done by AASHTO and the importance of upgrading infrastructure for economic growth and improved quality of life.